    = HTML provide us with elements that we can use to markup these section of the page based
      on their function.
      =<header> element     => for the common information at the top of the page like a logo or
                               main title
                            => can be use at the top of a section element 
      = <Nav> element       => for the navigation bar which is usually just a series of links.
      = <main> element      => represent the main contents of a document.
      = <article> element   => represent a standalone piece of content like news article or blog post.
      = <section> element   => it's similar to the article but the section doesn't have a semantic meaning.
      = <aside> element     => for content that's related to the main content often shown in sidebar
      = <footer> element    => which typically contains information about an author or copyright information. 
    = <div> element create a new line and <span> element shown in line with the rest of the sorrounding content.